          </equation>
          </item> <item> <label> Write the final answer </label>
          <para id="id650261">The equivalent resistance of two <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mspace width="2pt"/><m:mi mathvariant="normal">k</m:mi><m:mi>Ω</m:mi></m:math> resistors connected in parallel is <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mspace width="2pt"/><m:mi mathvariant="normal">k</m:mi><m:mi>Ω</m:mi></m:math>. </para>
          </item> </list> </solution>
</exercise><exercise id="eip-994"><problem id="probfhsst_id10102">
          <para id="id651098">Two resistors are connected in parallel. The equivalent resistance is <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mspace width="2pt"/> <m:mi>Ω</m:mi></m:math>. If one resistor is  <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mn>150</m:mn><m:mspace width="2pt"/><m:mi>Ω</m:mi></m:math>, calculate the value of the second resistor. </para>
          </problem>
          <solution id="solfhsst_id11005"> <list id="listfhsst_id10905" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
          <item> <label> Determine how to approach the problem </label>
          <para id="id6512152">Since the resistors are in parallel we can use:</para>
          <equation id="id651555">
            <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
              <m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                </m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
               <m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </equation>
          <para id="id6519212">We are given the value of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub></m:math>.</para>
          </item> <item> <label> Solve the problem </label>
          <equation id="id6523230">
            <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
              <m:mtable displaystyle="true">
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                   <m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                </m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>1</m:mi>
